Birds requires the following libraries:
    *Pygame
    *numpy
    *scipy

To install these libraries on Linux, use:

➜ sudo apt-get install python-pip 
➜ sudo apt-get install libatlas-base-dev gfortran
➜ sudo pip install scipy
➜ sudo apt-get install python-pygame


Build instructions:
To run Birds, enter the 'Birds' directory and use:

➜ python setup.py build build_ext --inplace

This builds the diffusion Numpy extension 'diffuse.c' as a runnable Python module called 'diffuse.so' using the extension found in 'setup.py'.

Then, simply run the Main.py file with python, using:

➜ python Main.py